race.comment: This doesn't look a maiden with huge depth. ISOTROPIC (7) has placed in two of her eight career starts but was well held at her first run for the new stable but she got a long way back there and was OK to the line. She steps straight to 1600m and is open to sharp improvement. Suspect she might be able to run a race at a big price. FLAMING EYES (6) drops back from 2050m and has been in the minor money over this track and trip. He's rock hard fit and Holder might be able to use that to his advantage. He is a definite winning chance. LUDINA (10) is a three-year-old who was doing her best work late over 1400m last time out. The extra 200m suits and she's drawn to get the run of the race with no weight on her back. She can be in the finish. Including THE PUNK ROCKER (5) and I AM RALPH (3) in wider plays but the race drops away from there.
